main event: A bright light was observed in the sky over Parkersburg, West Virginia on October 17, 1968.
interesting points: The light appeared to increase and disappear over the horizon in about 20 seconds.
The observer described the light as being like a light bulb, almost circular in shape, and pulsating in a rapid manner.
The light was estimated to be about 250 feet above the trees and very close to the observer.
The observer was unable to determine the angular size or estimate the actual size of the object.
The observer did not notice any sound coming from the object, nor any effect on the ground or any machinery in the vicinity.
sighted object: A bright light in the sky
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
